من زنم آقا ببخشید ، من سیاسر نیستم
کوه الماسین عشقم سنگ مرمر نیستم

مادر مولای روم شمس تبریزی منم
من همینم جنس زیر چادر که دیدی نیستم

معنی شعرم ، شکوه شاعر دولت منم
پاسبان خانه و جارو کش در نیستم

وای برحالم که زیر چادری پوسیده ام
من ز نسل آدمم ، تندیس آذر نیستم

از شب اندیشان نجویم حس استقلال خویش
سنگ سارم میکنند من میدانم خر نیستم

چادری شرط مسلمان بودن من نیست، پس
من بیدون چادری تان هم که کافر نیستم

مردها ! این مردسالاری چی معنی میدهد
مشکل اش این مه مثل شما مرد نیستم

هوش کن سنگم نزن نازکتر از رویاستم
در شکستن هم که از آینه کمتر نیستم

It was an honor to share my story at Harvard Kennedy School. I shared the challenges an Afghan woman athlete including cyclists, faces from the beginning until now. Thank you @jamiemittelman for inviting me and thank you @harvardkennedyschool for having me there. It was a great honor to be among some of the world's great woman Olympian athletes as my panelists. The event “Women Empowerment” @flamebearers is organized for powerful women around us whether in sports, politics, or in games. It’s a perfect platform to showcase successful women who have gone through tons of challenges. 
And most of all, I am more than proud to represent myself as an Afghan Athlete. I wore our beautiful Afghan traditional dress from @zaricollectionaf . It’s a beautiful black cherma dress which is made all by hand embroidered.

@refugeenetwork Thank you so much for making this opportunity to share my story with women refugees from all over the world.

I want to extend my heartfelt appreciation to the Women Refugee Network @refugeenetwork @templemoore04 for their kindness in hosting and inviting me to be a part of their community. It was an incredible experience to join them in training new cyclists. Their dedication to empowering women refugees and providing them with opportunities for growth is truly inspiring. The warmth and support I received from everyone involved made the experience even more meaningful. Thank you for creating a space where we can come together, learn, and uplift each other. Your efforts are making a positive impact on the lives of many, and I am grateful to have been a part of it. Thank you so much Meena jan for everything!
